body_html: The _image_type() function is placeholder logic that needs to go into a separate TensorFlow operation. The code currently pushed works if pre-loaded bytes are sent to the Op, but will crash and burn if the output from another op is passed in (say, from tf.read_file())

body: The `_image_type()` function is placeholder logic that needs to go into a separate TensorFlow operation. The code currently pushed works if pre-loaded bytes are sent to the Op, but will crash and burn if the output from another op is passed in (say, from `tf.read_file()`)
